                            </div>
                            <div class="collapse" id="collapse5" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-parent="#faqAccordion">
                                <div class="card-body  bg-light">
                                    <p>Our negotiation rate ranges from 30% to 50%, meaning we usually save you 30% to 50% on your overall outstanding. Our Expert Debt Advisors (EDAs) know exactly how to deal with each lender and look for solutions that support your cause to save maximum with each lender. We won’t stop until we’ve reached the best deal possible. We Promise.</p>

                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card border-0 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.4s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                            <div class="card-header shadow  bg-light" id="heading6">
                                <h6 class="mb-0 collapsed h5" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse6" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseThree">How long will it take to get out of debt? <span class="lni-chevron-up"></span></h6>
                            </div>
                            <div class="collapse" id="collapse6" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-parent="#faqAccordion">
                                <div class="card-body  bg-light">
                                    <p>
                                        It depends on how quickly you can build up your funds and save for the settlement offers. The faster you save, the quicker you get out of debt.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card border-0 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.4s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                            <div class="card-header shadow  bg-light" id="heading7">
                                <h6 class="mb-0 collapsed h5" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse7" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseThree">Will I get sued by my lenders?  <span class="lni-chevron-up"></span></h6>
                            </div>
                            <div class="collapse" id="collapse7" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-parent="#faqAccordion">
                                <div class="card-body  bg-light">
                                    <p>
                                        There is a slight possibility that a lender might sue you. But, lawsuits are expensive and lenders try to avoid them. We aim to complete the program as quickly as possible to avoid any lawsuits.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card border-0 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.4s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                            <div class="card-header shadow  bg-light" id="heading8">
                                <h6 class="mb-0 collapsed h5" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse8" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseThree">Is Debt/Loan Settlement really, worth it?<span class="lni-chevron-up"></span></h6>
                            </div>
                            <div class="collapse" id="collapse8" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-parent="#faqAccordion">
                                <div class="card-body  bg-light">
                                    <p>
                                        Yes! Absolutely!

                                        Debt is a valuable tool when used wisely. A home loan can help you move into your dream home and an auto loan can help you buy your dream car. Credit cards are a plus for your finances if you use them for the perks and rewards without letting them take over your life. Even a Personal Loan that finances your urgent needs are helpful.

                                        But if your debt has gotten out of control and you are revolving Debt/Loan at exorbitant charges or struggling to make minimum payments on your Credit Cards, you’re dealing with unnecessary stress that can affect both you and those close to you.

                                        CONFIRM will help you manage it and provide a path out of debt that could result in you paying less than you owe. When you enrol in our program, not only will we negotiate down your debt and help you get on top of your finances, but you’ll also find yourself free of the stress, guilt, and worry that comes with overwhelming debt. That means you’ll have time to focus on what really matters: family, career, and enjoying life to the fullest.
                                </div>
